							<h3 align="center"> FDDI participates in ‘National Rubber Conference 2022’ organized by AIRIA, Eastern Region </h3>

						<p align="justify"> Footwear Design & Development Institute (FDDI) participated in National Rubber Conference (NRC) 2022 which was organized by All India Rubber Industries Association (AIRIA), Eastern Region and held on 4th & 5th of January 2023 at Rangmaanch, Raajkutir, Swabhumi, Kolkata. </p>
						<p align="justify"> AIRIA is a not for profit making body serving the rubber industry and trade with the objectives of safeguarding and promoting interests of the industry. </p>
						<p align="justify"> The event was graced by the esteemed presence of dignitaries like Dr. Shashi Panja, Hon’ble Minister for Industries, Commerce & Enterprises and Department of Women & Child Development and Social Welfare, Government of West Bengal as the ‘Chief Guest’, whereas Mr. Arun Kumar Sinha, IAS, Managing Director (MD) - FDDI, Prof. Dr. Sawar Dhanania, Chairman - Rubber Board and Mr. Anirudh K. Bharti, ED - RDSO were the ‘Guest of Honour(s)’ of the event. </p>
																																																																
						<span class="news-details-img">
						<img class="img-responsive" src="img/new@fddi/rubber-conf-2022.JPG" alt="img">						
						</span>

						<p align="justify"> The theme of the two-day’s conference was ‘Indian Rubber Industry 2.0: Shifting Gears’, during which many technical experts and like-minded individuals from across the country and the globe from Tyre/ Rubber/ Machinery and Allied Industry and prominent technical and management institutions made presentation in six sessions covering new ideas, technologies and opportunities for growth in the rubber sector. </p>
						<p align="justify"> Delivering the ‘Keynote Address’, Mr. Arun Kumar Sinha, IAS, MD, FDDI, said, “In the modern world, we use, feel, and see many rubber products and its applications spread across many important industries, such as the chemical, transportation, agriculture, and aerospace industries. On the manufacturing front, manufacturers of rubber products and rubber processors play a key role in the development of non-leather footwear too.” </p>
						<p align="justify"> In his address, Mr. Sinha further said, “Considering the ever increasing role of non-leather footwear, of which rubber is one of the major constituent, FDDI is being empowered by the Ministry to bring up world class infrastructure and the skills second to none through upgradation of its Rohtak and Jodhpur campus into "Centres of Excellence (CoE),” on the thematic area of Center for Non-Leather Footwear, Products & Accessories and High Performance/ Specialized Footwear & Products and Start-Ups respectively.” </p>
						
						<span class="news-details-img">
						<img class="img-responsive" src="img/new@fddi/rubber-conf-2022-1.JPG" alt="img">						
						</span>
						
						<p align="justify"> “These CoE’s that have been established are in sync with each other as the Biomechanics lab & Polymer Lab setup at Rohtak will help to create the data for the artificial foot & limb which will be used in Jodhpur to take out the output through high precision 3D printer. These CoEs are also expected to create R&D capacities in specific areas of specialization to address critical shortage of knowledge base in emerging technologies,” added Mr. Sinha. </p>
						<p align="justify"> FDDI also gave a presentation on ‘Design & Process Technology’ on the 2nd day of the conference i.e. 5th January 2023. The presentation was given by Mr. Ramesh Chandra Sahoo, HoD-FDP. During the presentation, he emphasized on the various activities of FDDI for the development of footwear industry & and design & process technology advancements’ being adopted by the footwear industry. </p>
						<p align="justify"> NRC was a perfect forum to discuss the new innovations taking place globally in the field of Rubber /Footwear Technology & allied fields. </p>
						<p align="justify"> During the NRC 2022, the students of FDDI Kolkata campus displayed a wide range of creations at its stall that included ladies & gents shoes, casual and formal footwear and sports shoes. </p>
						
						<span class="news-details-img">
						<img class="img-responsive" src="img/new@fddi/rubber-conf-2022-2.JPG" alt="img">						
						</span>						
						
						<p align="justify"> The students of FDDI Kolkata campus also participated in the ‘Fashion Show’ on 5th of January 2023 and presented their footwear collections. </p>
						<p align="justify"> The programme was graced by the presence of Padmashree, Ms. Jhulan Goswami, Ace Indian Cricketer. She praised the efforts of FDDI and Indian rubber and footwear industry. She hoped that one day will come when Indian brands will bring out shoes for the playing fraternity. </p>
						<p align="justify"> The eye catching collections were appreciated by one and all present during the show and also received accolade from the entire media. </p>
						<p align="justify"> Sharing the details, Mr. Sinha said, “The fashion show organized during the NRC 2022 by AIRIA, Eastern Region provided the budding designers of FDDI a platform to showcase their creativity, innovation and designing capabilities of both leather and non-leather footwear in consonance with the industry latest trends.” </p>
						<p align="justify"> The deliberations of the eminent business professionals of rubber industry and trade invited for the conference paved way for technological advancement and provide new impetus to the rubber industry. </p>
						<p align="justify"> Aligning with the theme i.e., ‘Indian Rubber Industry 2.0 Shifting Gears’, the conference played a transformative role in fulfilling the goals of Hon’ble Prime Minister’s ‘Vocal for Local’, ‘Make in India’ and ‘Aatmanirbhar Bharat’. </p>
								
																																																																
